obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30653)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30653&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Co-operative`
  line `Development Corporation Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 32 of 1973, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-8-1973).`
  line
  line `2. 14th March, 1963, vide notification No. G.S.R. 456, dated 14th March, 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30654)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30654&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "agricultural produce" includes the following:--`
  line
  line `(i) edible and non-edible oil seeds;`
  line
  line `(ii) cattle feed, including oilcakes and other ingredients;`
  line
  line `(iii) produce of horticulture and animal husbandry;`
  line
  line `(iv) produce of forestry;`
  line
  line `(v) produce of poultry farming;`
  line
  line `(vi) produce of pisciculture; and`
  line
  line `(vii) produce of other allied activities, whether or not undertaken jointly with agriculture;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) “bank” means a nationalised bank and includes a scheduled bank;`
  line
  line `(ab) “Board” means the Board of Management of the Corporation constituted under section 10;]`
  line
  line `^3[(aba) "Central financing institution" means Industrial Development Bank of India established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964)`
  line `or the Industrial Finance Corporation of India Limited, a company formed and registered under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or the Industrial Credit and Investment Corporation of India`
  line `Limited, a Company formed and registered under the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913);]`
  line
  line `^4[(b) "Central Warehousing Corporation" means the Central Warehousing Corporation`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Warehousing Corporations Act, 1962 (58 of`
  line `1962);`
  line
  line `(c) "co-operative society" means a society registered or deemed to be registered under the`
  line `Co-operative Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912) or under the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act,`
  line `1984 (51 of 1984) or under any other law with respect to cooperative societies for the time being in`
  line `force in any State, which is engaged in any of the activities specified in sub-section (1) of section 9`
  line `and includes a Co-operative Land Development Bank, by whatever name called;]`
  line
  line `(d) "Corporation" means the National Co-operative Development Corporation established under`
  line `^5[sub-section (1) of section 3];`
  line
  line `^6[(da) "foodstuffs", include--`
  line
  line `(i) coconuts and areca-nuts;`
  line
  line `(ii) eggs and egg products;`
  line
  line `(iii) fish, whether fresh, frozen, dried or preserved;`
  line
  line `(iv) fruits, whether fresh, dried or dehydrated;`
  line
  line `(v) honey;`
  line
  line `(vi) meat, whether fresh, frozen, dried or preserved;`
  line
  line `(vii) milk and milk products;`
  line
  line `(viii) vegetables;`
  line
  line `(db) "General Council" means the General Council of the Corporation constituted under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^7[(dba) "industrial goods" means the products of industrial co-operatives or cottage and village`
  line `industries or products of allied industries in the rural area and includes any handicrafts or rural crafts;`
  line
  line `(dbb) "livestock" includes all animals to be raised for milk, meat, fleece, skin, wool and other byproducts;]`
  line
  line `(dc) "Managing director" means the managing director of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `^8[(dd) "nationalised bank" means a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or under`
  line `section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of`
  line `1980);]]`
  line
  line `(e) "notified commodity" means any commodity (other than agricultural produce 2`
  line [and
  line `foodstuffs]) which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be`
  line `a notified commodity for the purposes of this Act, being a commodity with respect to which`
  line `Parliament has power to make laws by virtue of entry 33 in List III in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `^7[(ea) "notified services" means any service which the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, declare to be notified services for the purposes of this Act;]`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `^6[(ga) "scheduled bank" means a bank for the time being included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);]`
  line
  line `^9[(h) “State Bank” means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India Act,`
  line `1955 (23 of 1955)or any of the subsidiary banks of the State Bank of India;`
  line
  line `(ha) "State Co-operative Bank" has the same meaning as in the National Bank for Agriculture`
  line `and Rural Development Act, 1981 (61 of 1981);]`
  line
  line `(i) "year" means the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 3, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clauses (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 3, for section 3 (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (dd) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 3, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002)`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (30655)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references to any law not in force or any functionary not existence in the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30655&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. [Construction of references to any law not in force or any functionary not existence in the`
  line `State of Jammu and Kashmir*].--Omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central`
  line `Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020)`
  line
  line `and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020). ]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 21-8-1973).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30656)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of the National Co-operative Development Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30656&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified in the notification, a Corporation by the name of the National Co-operative Development`
  line `Corporation which shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal with power`
  line `to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and may, in the said name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The head-office of the Corporation shall be in New Delhi.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The Corporation shall carry on its functions through the General Council and the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The General Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a President and a Vice-President, both to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) eight members, ex officio, to be nominated by the Central Government from such of its`
  line `Ministries dealing with economic matters as it may think fit;`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) Chairman of the National Bank of Agriculture and Rural Development constituted under`
  line `the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981 (61 of 1981), ex officio;]`
  line
  line `(iv) Managing Director of the State Bank, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) Managing Director of the Food Corporation of India, constituted under the Food Corporations`
  line `Act, 1964, (37 of 1964) ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) Managing Director of the Central Warehousing Corporation, constituted under the`
  line `Warehousing Corporations Act, 1962 (59 of 1962), ex officio;`
  line
  line `^3[(vii) one member to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the chairmen of`
  line `one of the Central financing institutions, ex officio;]`
  line
  line `(viii) a member representing banks, to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ix) Chairman of the National Co-operative Union of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(x) Chairman of the National Agricultural Co-operative Marketing Federation, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xi) Chairman of the National Federation of Co-operative Sugar Factories, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xii) Chairman of the All India Federation of Co-operative Spinning Mills, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xiii) Chairman of the All India State Co-operative Banks,Federation, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xiv) eleven members, other than those nominated under clause (xv), representing the States and`
  line `the Union territories, to be nominated by the Central Government, provided that not more than one`
  line `person shall be so nominated from each State or Union territory;`
  line
  line `(xv) eleven members to be nominated by the Central Government from among the Chairmen of`
  line `the State level co-operative federations from the States and Union territories, provided that not more`
  line `than one person shall be so nominated from each State or Union territory;`
  line
  line `(xvi) four members representing persons having special knowledge of, or practical experience in,`
  line `agricultural co-operative development, to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xvii) ^4[fourmembers] representing national level organisations engaged or interested in the`
  line `promotion and development of co-operative programmes, to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(xviii) the managing director.`
  line
  line `(5) The powers and functions of the Corporation shall be exercised or discharged, as the case may be,`
  line `by the General Council, and references elsewhere in this Act to the Corporation shall, unless the context`
  line `otherwise requires, be construed as references to the General Council.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding the expiry of the prescribed term of his office, every member of the General`
  line `Council shall continue to hold office as such, until his successor in such office has assumed charge of`
  line `such office.`
  line
  line `(7) Members of the General Council, other than the managing director, shall be entitled to receive`
  line `such sitting fees as may be specified by regulations made by the Corporation under this Act, for attending`
  line `any meeting of the General Council, Board or any committee of the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no official member shall be entitled to receive any sitting fee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 4, for sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 4, for clauses (iii) and (iv) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (vii) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 4, for "three members" (w.e.f. 16-9-2002)`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30657)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualifications for being a member of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30657&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being`
  line `chosen as, and for being, a member of the Corporation--`
  line
  line `(i) if he is, or at any time has been, adjudicated insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts`
  line `or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if he is or has been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced in`
  line `respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months, unless a period of five years has elapsed`
  line `from the date of expiry of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(iii) ^1[except in the case of managing director,] if he is a salaried official of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30658)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of members of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30658&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of members of the`
  line `Corporation and the manner of filling vacancies among members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any member of the Corporation other than an ex officio member may resign his office by giving`
  line `notice in writing to the Central Government and on such resignation being accepted, he shall be deemed`
  line `to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30659)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal from office of member, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30659&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, at any time, remove from`
  line `office any member other than an ex officio member of the Corporation after giving him a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the proposed removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30660)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Meetings, etc., of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30660&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation ^1[shall ordinarily meet twice a year at such`
  line `times] and places and shall, subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), observe such procedure`
  line `in regard to transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be provided`
  line `by regulations made by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[President] or, in his absence, the ^3[Vice-President] or, in the absence of both the ^2[President]`
  line `^2[President] and the ^3[Vice-President], any member chosen by the members present from amongst`
  line `themselves, shall preside at a meeting of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions at a meeting of the Corporation shall be decided by a majority of votes of the`
  line `members present and voting, and in the case of an equality of votes, the ^4[President] or, in his absence, the`
  line `^5[Vice-President] or, in the absence of both the ^4[President] and the ^5[Vice-President], the person`
  line `presiding shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "shall meet at such times" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Chairman" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 6, for "Chairman" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30661)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Officers and other employees of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30661&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, in`
  line `consultation with the Corporation, appoint a person to be the ^1`
  line `[managing director].`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the Corporation`
  line `may appoint such other officers and employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay of the officers and`
  line `other employees of the Corporation shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) as respects the ^2`
  line `[managing director], be such as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) as respects the other officers and employees, be such as may be determined by regulations`
  line `made by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(4) The managing director shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as the Board may`
  line `entrust or delegate to him.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "Secretary of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "Secretary" (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30662)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30662&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the functions of the`
  line `Corporation shall be to ^2`
  line `[plan, promote and finance]programmes, through co-operative societies, for--`
  line
  line `(a) the production, processing, marketing, storage, export and import of agricultural produce,`
  line `foodstuffs, poultry feed and notified commodities;`
  line
  line `(b) the collection, processing, marketing, storage and export of minor forest produce;]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(c)development of notified services.]`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the Corporation`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) advance loans or grant subsidies to State Governments for financing co-operative societies`
  line `and for employment of staff for implementing programmes of co-operative development;`
  line
  line `(b) provide funds to State Governments for financing co-operative societies for the purchase of`
  line ^4
  line `[agricultural produce, foodstuffs] ^5[livestock, poultry feed, industrial goods, notified commodities`
  line `and notified services] on behalf of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) plan and promote programmes through co-operative societies for the supply of seeds,`
  line `manures, fertilizers, agricultural implements and other articles for the development of agricultural`
  line produce;
  line
  line `^6[(d) provide loans and grants directly to the national level co-operative societies and other cooperative societies having objects extending beyond one State;`
  line
  line `(e) provide loans to co-operative societies on the guarantee of State Governments or in the case of`
  line `co-operative societies in the Union territories, on the guarantee of Central Government:`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[Providedthat no such guarantee shall be required in cases in which security to thesatisfaction of`
  line `the Corporation is furnished by the borrowing co-operativesociety;]`
  line
  line `(f) participate in the share capital of the national level co-operative societies and other`
  line `co-operative societies having objects extending beyond one State.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall so exercise its functions under this section as not to interfere with the`
  line `activities of the Khadi and Village Industries Commission established under the Khadi and Village`
  line `Industries Commission Act, 1956 (61 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 5, for "plan and promote" (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 8, for "agricultural produce" (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 5, for "and notified commodities" (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 8. (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `7. The proviso ins. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 5 (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30663)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Board of Management of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 9, for section 10 (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30663&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[10. Board of Management of the Corporation.--(1) There shall be a Board of Management of the`
  line `the Corporation which shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Vice-President of the General Council, who shall be the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(ii) three members of the General Council, to be nominated by the Central Government from`
  line `among the members referred to in clause (ii) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(iii) the member of the General Council, referred to in clause (iii) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(iv) one member of the General Council, to be nominated by the Central Government from among`
  line `the members referred to in clauses (ix), (x), (xi), (xii) and (xiii) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(v) two members of the General Council, to be nominated by the Central Government from`
  line `among the members referred to in clause (xiv) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(vi) two members of the General Council, to be nominated by the Central Government from`
  line `among the members referred to in clause (xv) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(vii) one member of the General Council, to be nominated by the Central Government from`
  line `among the members referred to in clauses (xvi) and (xvii) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(viii) the managing director.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-Chairman of the Board shall be nominated by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general control, direction and superintendence of the General Council, the Board`
  line `shall be competent to deal with any matter within the competence of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall meet at such times and at such places and shall observe such procedure in regard`
  line `to transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be provided by`
  line `regulations made by the Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The confirmed minutes of every meeting of the Board shall be laid before the General Council at`
  line `its next following meeting.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (30664)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30664&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may constitute such other committees for general or`
  line `special purposes as it deems necessary for the efficient performance of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (30665)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Grants by the Central Government to Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30665&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) by way of grant each year, such sum of money as is required by the Corporation for giving`
  line `subsidies to State Governments and for meeting its administrative expenses;^1`
  line ***
  line
  line `(b) by way of loan, such sum of money on such terms and conditions as the Central Government`
  line `may determine; ^2[and]`
  line
  line `^2[(c) such additional grants, if any, for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word and omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (30666)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Corporation to borrow money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30666&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Power of Corporation to borrow money.--(1) The Corporation may, for the purposes of`
  line `carrying out its functions under this Act, and with the previous approval of, and subject to the directions`
  line `of the Central Government, borrow money from--`
  line
  line `(a) the public by the issue or sale of bonds or debentures, or both, carrying interest at such rates`
  line `as may be specified therein;`
  line
  line `(b) any bank or other financial institution;`
  line
  line `(c) any other authority, organisation or institution as may be specially approved by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may guarantee the repayment of the moneys borrowed by the`
  line `Corporation under clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) and the payment of interest`
  line `thereon and other incidental charges.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (30667)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 15
  title `Grants, donations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30667&sectionno=12B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Grants, donations, etc.--(1) The Corporation may receive gifts, grants, donations or`
  line `benefactions from Government or any other agency in or outside India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall not receive any gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from a foreign`
  line `government or, any other agency outside India except with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (30668)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Corporation to maintain fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30668&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall maintain a fund called the National`
  line `Co-operative Development Fund (hereinafter referred to as the Fund) to which shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys and other securities transferred to it under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section`
  line 24;
  line
  line `(b) the grants and other sums of money by way of loans paid to the Corporation by the Central`
  line `Government under section 12;`
  line
  line `^1[(bb) all moneys received under section 12B;`
  line
  line `(bbb) all moneys received for services rendered;]`
  line
  line `^2[(ba) all moneys borrowed under section 12A;]`
  line
  line `(c) such additional grants, if any, as the Central Government may make to the Corporation for the`
  line `purposes of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) such sums of money as may, from time to time, be realised out of repayment of loans made`
  line `from the Fund or from interest on loans or dividends ^2[or other realisations] on investments made`
  line `from the Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The moneys in the Fund shall be applied for--`
  line
  line `(a) advancing loans and granting subsidies to State Governments on such terms and conditions as`
  line `the Corporation may deem fit for the purpose of enabling State Governments to subscribe to the share`
  line `capital of co-operative societies or for otherwise financing co-operative societies;`
  line
  line `(b) meetingthe pay and allowances of the ^3[managing director, the officers] and other employees`
  line `of the Corporation and other administrative expenses of the Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(c) carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) All moneys in the Fund shall be deposited in the Reserve Bank or the State Bank or a`
  line `nationalised bank or a scheduled bank or a State Co-operative Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-8-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 12(w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "officers" (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 45 of 2002, s. 7, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 16-9-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (30669)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30669&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall furnish to the Central Government at such`
  line `times and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such`
  line `returns and statements and such particulars in regard to the discharge of its functions under this Act as the`
  line `Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Corporation shall, as soon as possible,`
  line `after the end of each year, submit to the Central Government a report, in such form and manner and`
  line `before such date as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and`
  line `programme during the previous year.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (30670)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30670&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `In all matters including matters of policy, the Corporation`
  line `shall be guided by such directions as may be given to it by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (30671)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title `Submission of programme of activities and financial estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30671&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall`
  line `prepare before the commencement of each year a statement of programme of its activities during the`
  line `forthcoming year as well as a financial estimate in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) A statement prepared under sub-section (1) shall, not later than three months before the`
  line `commencement of each year, be submitted to the Central Government for approval.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (30672)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Accounts of Board and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30672&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The account of the Corporation shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India or any person authorised by him in this behalf and any expenditure incurred in connection with`
  line `such audit shall be payable by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person authorised by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Corporation shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books,`
  line `accounnts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any office of the`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Corporation certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person authorised by him in this behalf together with an audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (30673)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate acts and proceedings of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 13, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30673&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No act or`
  line `proceeding of ^1[the General Council, the Board or any of the committees of the Corporation] shall be`
  line `invalid by reason only of the existence of any vacancy among its members or any defect in the`
  line `constitution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (30674)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "Chairman or the Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30674&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the`
  line `^1[President or the Vice-President] or any other member or any officer of the Corporation subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order such of its powers and functions under`
  line `this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (30675)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Declaration of fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30675&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every member, auditor, officer or other employee of the`
  line `Corporation shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form`
  line `set out in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (30676)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Dissolution of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30676&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, if it is of opinion that the`
  line `Corporation has failed to carry out its functions under this Act or that for any other reason it is not necessary to continue the Corporation, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, dissolve the`
  line `Corporation from such date as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Corporation is dissolved under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members of the Corporation shall, from the date of dissolution, vacate their offices as such`
  line members;
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Corporation shall, as from the date of dissolution, be exercised`
  line `and performed by the Central Government or such person or persons as the Central Government may`
  line `appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys and other properties of the Corporation shall vest in the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (30677)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30677&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) the term of office of members of the Corporation and the manner of filling vacancies among`
  line them;
  line
  line `(e) the methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scale of pay of the ^2[managing`
  line director];
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(g) the returns, statements and other particulars in regard to the discharge of its functions to be`
  line `furnished by the Corporation to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and the manner in which, and the time within which, the Corporation shall furnish to`
  line `the Central Government returns, statements and other particulars with regard to the discharge of its`
  line functions;
  line
  line `(i) the form and the manner in which, and the time within which, the Corporation shall furnish to`
  line `the Central Government a report of its activities, policy and programme;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session ^4[or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before theexpiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clauses (a), (b) and (c) omitted by Act 3 of 1974, s. 15 (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Secretary to the Corporation" (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (f) omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1973, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 21-8-1973).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (30678)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Corporation to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30678&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provision is`
  line `necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which meetings of ^1[the General Council, the Board and other committees of`
  line `the Corporation] shall be convened, the fees for attending such meetings and the procedure to be`
  line `followed thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) the methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay of the officers`
  line `(other than the ^2[managing director]) and other employees of the Corporations;`
  line
  line `(c) the duties and conduct of officers and other employees of the Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter in respect of which the Corporation is empowered or required to make`
  line `regulations under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, rescind any regulation`
  line `which it has sanctioned and thereupon the regulation shall cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1974, s. 16, for "the Corporation, the Executive Committee and other committees thereof" (w.e.f. 7-4-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "Secretary" (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (30679)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885&sectionId=30679&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00001_196226_1517807317885
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from the date on which the Corporation is established under`
  line `section 3, the Agricultural Produce (Development and Warehousing) Corporations Act, 1956 (28 of`
  line `1956), shall, in so far as it relates to the National Co-operative Development and Warehousing Board,`
  line `stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys and other securities belonging to the National Co-operative Development Fund`
  line `which, immediately before the said date, was maintained by the National Co-operative Development`
  line `and Warehousing Board established under the repealed Act (hereinafter referred to as the said Board),`
  line `shall stand transferred to, and be maintained by, the Corporation established under section 3 of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(b) all moneys and other securities belonging to the National Warehousing Development Fund`
  line `which, immediately before the said date, was maintained by the said Board under the repealed Act,`
  line `shall stand transferred to and be maintained by the Central Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) all shares in the capital of the Central Warehousing Corporation held by the said Board shall`
  line `stand transferred to the Central Government subject to the same liabilities as to payment of unpaid`
  line `calls on such shares as the said Board was subject to;`
  line
  line `(d) anything done or any action taken (including any loan advanced, subsidy granted and`
  line `appointment, delegation, rule or regulation made) under the repealed Act shall, in so far as it is not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(e) all rights, liabilities and obligations of the said Board, whether arising out of any contract or`
  line `otherwise, shall be the rights, liabilities and obligations respectively of the Corporation established`
  line `under section 3 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
